                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Cabinet Committee on Germany met with Roosevelt on September 6, 1944, and
                    discussed the memoranda prepared by the State, War, and Treasury Departments
                        (<hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_95">pp. 95</ref>, <ref
                        target="#pg_98">98</ref>, and <ref target="#pg_101">101</ref>,
                    respectively). No official minutes of the meeting have been found, but
                    information on the meeting is included in Hull, p. 1609; Stimson and Bundy, pp.
                    573–574; and Morgenthau material printed in Blum, pp. 362–363, and <hi
                        rend="italic">Morgenthau Diary</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Germany</hi>), vol.
                    I, pp. 536–538.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
